The paper deals with optimizing the performance of convolutional neural nets (CNNs) by minimizing data movement, which is a key concern in distributed computing and parallel processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CV seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on optimizing the computational efficiency of CNNs, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures for processing large amounts of image data. The other categories are also relevant, as they deal with various aspects of machine learning and neural networks, but may be less likely given the specific focus of the paper.
